Meningococcal disease, serogroup W135 - Update
------------------------------------------------
This update concerns cases of meningococcal disease associated with
international travel and reported previously on 3 May; 27 April; 26 April;
20 April; 11 April as well as confirmed cases of _Neisseria meningitidis_
serogroup W135. New and revised notifications of these cases from 28 Feb
2000 have been received from the following countries:
Country Cases /Deaths
Finland 1
France 18/ 4
Germany 2
Iran 56
Italy 0
Kuwait 1
Morocco 3/ 1
Netherlands 6
Oman 18/ 2
Saudi Arabia 241/ 59
Singapore 4
Spain 0
United Kingdom 31/ 5
United States 3
WHO is actively monitoring the situation and requesting countries to send
specimens to WHO Collaborating Centres for Meningococcal Infections so that
the strains can be fully identified and traced. The Centres are:
Institut de Medecine Tropicale du Service de Sante des Armees
Parc du Pharo, B.P. 46
